If you run a meetup or are aware of a group of people meeting and discussing Emacs, please add them here so other people can connect.

Meeting other Emacs geeks is a great way to pick up ideas and learn even more. Can't find an Emacs meetup near you? [http://harryrschwartz.com/2015/09/14/starting-an-emacs-meetup.html Here are a few tips on starting an Emacs meetup]. Have fun!

== Upcoming events ==

* EmacsSF (virtual): Emacs Lisp and menu packages: dmenu, hydra, posframe, transient, etc. https://www.meetup.com/Emacs-SF/events/276673677/ Fri Mar 5 1000 Vancouver / 1200 Chicago / 1300 Toronto / 1800 GMT / 1900 Berlin / 2330 Kolkata – Sat Mar 6 0200 Singapore
* EmacsNYC: Mail Month https://emacsnyc.org/2021/02/03/monthly-online-meetup-mail-month.html Mon Mar 1 1600 Vancouver / 1800 Chicago / 1900 Toronto -- Tue Mar 2 0000 GMT / 0100 Berlin / 0530 Kolkata / 0800 Singapore
